  "text": "The Pearson correlation, r, is a measure of the linear dependence between two variables. It is one of the most commonly used statistical tools, especially in the social sciences (see [CITATION_1] , for a review in psychology). It is defined as r = cov (x, y) s (x) × s (y) ,",
